FBIS3-15226 "drsov042_h_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 Moldova Snegur To Sign `Partnership for Peace' Program AU0203132494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2015 GMT 1 Mar 94 AU0203132494 Chisinau BASAPRESS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS 1/3/1994 -- President Mircea Snegur met today with a NATO experts' group, arrived in Moldova to negotiate over the program "Partnership for Peace," [PFP] states the Presidential Press Service. Von Moltke, ambassador, deputy secretary general of NATO in charge of political problems, emphasized the importance of the program in stopping ethnic conflicts. In the opinion of Snegur, European structures should elaborate a mechanism of not admitting conflicts that threaten Europe. "From this point of view, the program `Partnership for Peace' seems to propose real solutions," said the president. The president reaffirmed his intention to sign this month the "Partnership for Peace," states the press service.
